---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="About Us - PuzzleCruise" description="About PuzzleCruise - The spoiler-free NYT Games hint progressive guide.">
    <Header />
    <main class="flex-grow w-full max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 space-y-8 text-gray-300">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-white mb-8">About PuzzleCruise</h1>
        
        <section class="space-y-4">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-100">Our Mission</h2>
            <p class="leading-relaxed text-lg">
                PuzzleCruise was founded by a group of passionate puzzle enthusiasts who love the daily challenge of New York Times games like Connections and Strands. 
                However, we noticed a major problem: when you get stuck and search for a hint online, most websites immediately spoil the entire answer! 
                That completely ruins the "Aha!" moment that makes these games so enjoyable.
            </p>
            <p class="leading-relaxed text-lg">
                That's why we built <strong>PuzzleCruise</strong>. Our goal is to provide a safe haven for players who just need a little nudge in the right direction. 
                We developed a unique, <strong>3-stage progressive hint system</strong> that gently guides you toward the solution without giving it away upfront.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4 mt-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-100">How We Do It</h2>
            <p class="leading-relaxed">
                Every day, our dedicated team solves the puzzles right at midnight and meticulously crafts progressive clues. 
                We analyze the "tricky" crossover words and build a strategy guide that helps you identify the traps before you waste your precious lives.
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-2 mt-4 text-gray-400">
                <li><strong>Stage 1:</strong> A gentle nudge about the category's theme.</li>
                <li><strong>Stage 2:</strong> A stronger hint, usually involving a synonym or starting letter.</li>
                <li><strong>Stage 3:</strong> The final answer, safely hidden behind spoiler warnings.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4 mt-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-100">Independent & Fan-Made</h2>
            <p class="leading-relaxed">
                PuzzleCruise is an independent, fan-run project. We are not affiliated with, sponsored by, or endorsed by The New York Times Company. 
                We are just puzzle lovers trying to help other puzzle lovers maintain their daily streaks with their pride intact.
            </p>
        </section>
    </main>
    <Footer />
</Layout>
